      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Combining melatonin and zolpidem can increase sedation and extend the time it takes to fall asleep before your body becomes too drowsy, so taking them together is generally not recommended without your doctor's explicit guidance. Always discuss combinations with your healthcare provider first, as they know your full medical history and prescription details. Prioritizing safety and proper medical advice is crucial before changing any sleep medication regimen.",
      "source": "target",
