      "content": "Melatonin and Ambien work differently on the brain's chemistry, so combining them often leads to excessive drowsiness rather than simply \"stacking\" their effects. Even without other substances, mixing these sedatives together is generally unnecessary and risky at this stage, as they can compound side effects like dizziness or confusion. It is best to follow your doctor's specific instructions for which medication to use alone rather than experimenting with combinations independently.",
